  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there were about 20 of these lined up, one against the other.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I have no idea what went on in the others.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were standing there, us, and-- and-- and there were these fires in the sky, these flames-- giant flames in the sky, as a building was burning.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so, in our innocence, we asked the next guy next-- standing next to us what [? in the hell ?] is burning?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he looked at us, big-eyed, and said, if we didn't know, he was not going to tell us because every day we didn't know was better for us.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it's really only bit by bit we found out what was going on.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you could see that from our-- from our rectangular-- [? yeah, ?] I forget the name of these.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The block was the house.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I don't remember the name of the-- of the compound, the whole compound.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I know it was Compound A.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But standing there in the evening, we could certainly see the-- the fire every night for-- for a while.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, of course, these, [? now ?] having been back at Birkenau-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] you know, I realize that next to this-- and, of course, also from reading-- I know that this was also the terminal of the-- of the railroad line inside of the camp, where people were unloaded from railroad trains and immediately gassed and burned, without ever, ever entering the-- the sort of Birkenau, the sort of Auschwitz camp that I was living in, which was, in fact, the work camp.",
      "word_count": 86
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The guard hadn't completely lied.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
